In this section, we consider problems involving the rates of change for two related variables.

For example, if the area of a metal frame, say \(A\), is related to the temperature of the metal frame, \(x\), by \(A=\mathrm{f}(x)\), how can we find the rate of change of \(A\) at a certain time \(t\), given the value of \(x\) and the rate of change of \(x\) at time \(t\)?

